Mildred Athletics
August 28 at 4:20 PM ¬∑

For those of you who are new to our Mildred family and a reminder to others.
Each year we sell Pink Out shirts to raise money for a local charity or as we did last year and will do again this year, provide gas vouchers for those individuals in Navarro County who are currently receiving treatments.
These vouchers are very much appreciated by those who receive them. We work with Mickey's Exxon and Texas Oncology plus we ask you if you know anyone who would benefit from these vouchers.

This year our Pink Out game for Football will be 9/25 and Volleyball 10/6 so this means, it's time to get those pink out shirts going!!
We have a bonus this year and we are offering Pink Out gaiters.
Please consider adding names to our shirts. Anyone you know who has faced any type of cancer!
We hope you will buy a shirt and a gaiter! Let's help others in our community!!

August 26 at 4:07 PM ¬∑

SAFETY GUIDELINES FOR HOME AND AWAY GAMES:
-All spectators must have a face covering on and properly worn over the mouth and nose when entering and exiting the gym/stadium.
-The UIL has stated that all spectators should make every effort to socially distance and to wear their face covering while in the stands.
- Face coverings must be worn while visiting the restrooms, concession stand and all common areas.
-Please do not enter the gym/stadium if you are displaying any symptoms of COVID-19.
-Spectators must remain in the gym/stadium stands during the game unless traveling to the restroom or concession stand.
** Elementary age children must be accompanied by a parent or guardian to and from the concession stand or restrooms.
** Students and spectators will not be allowed to congregate in any location of the gym/stadium.

August 1 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

Backpacks of Love distribution will be Tuesday and Wednesday, August 4th and 5th at Navarro College Cook Center 9 am - 7pm. This will be a drive thru event ONLY with 3 stations.

post_text:
Return to School Survey

School districts across Texas are struggling to answer one question: What will school be like next year because of COVID-19? We miss the face to face interaction with our students. Our aim is to reopen and allow students to attend classes on campus.

The first day of school is scheduled for August 12th. Please respond to this survey to help us plan for possible options.

By responding to this survey you are not committing to anything. Circumstances may change: however, sharing your thoughts is greatly appreciated. All submissions are anonymous.

Thank you very much for your time and support.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2N3NPRF

post_text:
Monday, April 13, MISD Junior High will distribute one packet per student that will contain work for the remainder of the school year. We will also be passing out the contents of each students locker.

To reduce handling of material and possible exposure to Covid-19, we will no longer have Monday pick-ups/drop-offs.

Completed work drop-offs will now be replaced with the use of grade level newspaper stands that will be available to return work at your own convenience. We expect work to be returned in a timely fashion, but the time frame you choose to return the work will be up to you.

Grade level stands will be located in front of the junior high entrance. Please make sure all work is labeled with the name of the student when you return work.

Teachers will still be available weekly for questions and assistance with assignments and work via email.

Please make sure this Monday, April 13 you turn in all your library books and classwork packets from week 1,2 and 3.

After careful consideration of the current Coronavirus information provided by the State of Texas, MISD will be closed March 16-20. At this time, school will resume on Monday, March 23. All school related events will be canceled. The University Interscholastic League has suspended all UIL sanctioned contests through March 29. Please know the health and well-being of our staff and students is of the utmost importance.

This situation is changing rapidly and we are receiving daily updates from Texas Education Agency. Please be prepared to be flexible as new information becomes available.

Shannon Baker
Mildred ISD

post_text:
New LOOK Coming to Parent Portal!!

To the Parent of MISD Student(s):

On November 2nd, our current parent portal system will transition to a new platform called Ascender.

Ascender ParentPortal is similar to that of TxConnect-Parent Portal. The parent's current sign-on and password will continue to work for the new system.

We are encouraging our parents/guardians to make sure ALL their students are linked to their account before November 2nd. This will help parents successfully login with immediate access to all their students without any delay. In addition, MISD is encouraging our parents to please verify the contact information for your child(ren). This is a great place to list people who can pick up your children from school for appointments or illness without the need to contact a parent/guardian. Please note, student data can ONLY be updated by the verified, enrolling parent.

If you have any questions, concerns or need technical support for your parent portal account, please email, easleyl@mildredisd.org or heugatterw@mildredisd.org
text:

On November 2nd, our current parent portal system will transition to a new platform called Ascender.

Ascender ParentPortal is similar to that of TxConnect-Parent Portal. The parent's current sign-on and password will continue to work for the new system.

We are encouraging our parents/guardians to make sure ALL their students are linked to their account before November 2nd. TEA Releases 2019 A-F Accountability Ratings:

This week TEA Released the 2019 A-F Accountability Ratings. Mildred ISD is pleased to announce that our District has achieved an over-all score of A. Mildred Independent School District is one of 257 districts within the State of Texas receiving the A rating. Students in Texas receive services in a total of 1022 districts. When you are out and about please congratulate our students and staff members on a job well done! If you are interested in more information regarding the A-F State ratings or the rating system, please visit the Texas Education Agency at tea.texas.gov.

post_text:
The Mildred ISD Board of Trustees approved pay raises for teachers, librarians, nurses, and counselors. Depending on years of experience, these employees will receive increases in pay ranging from 11% to 18%.

The Board of Trustees also chose to expand the scope of pay increases to other employee groups. Principals, secretaries, maintenance workers, bus drivers, teachers aides and cafeteria workers will see a 6% pay increase.

Thank you Board of Trustees for supporting the staff of MISD!

It will be Wednesday at the Mildred Baptist Church at 2:30.
We are asking for donations of sandwiches, pasta, fruit or any salads and desserts!
Paper products etc.
Your donation may be dropped off between 1 and 1:30 at the Baptist church or you my text 903 875 9729 to make other arrangements.
Please let us know what you will bring. You may reply to this post or text the number included.
Thank you!!

post_text:
We would like thank the Mildred Education Foundation (MEF) for their generosity this past school year. At the end of the year they gave out $6168.02 in grants to our faculty and staff and awarded $16,438.03 in wishlist items supporting our district personnel. Through the MEF, our district was blessed with totaling giving of $22,606.05.

Thank you to all the community members and businesses that support the MEF through fundraisers such as Denim and Diamonds.

If you would like to reach out to our foundation, the board members include:

Ellen Lewis
Ashley Hanna
Leslie Hayes
Robin Pritchett
Beth Horner
Michael Robinson
Kelly Daviss
Jason Payne
Shannon Baker
Angela Gassiott
Donna Springer
Samantha Daviss
Paula McNeel

#MildredRocks #MEF #EagleforLife

SPED Teacher (grades 6-12) Opening for 2019-2020 School Year

Position - Texas Certified SPED Teacher grades 6-12

Salary -
$4,000 plus State Base with Bachelor's Degree

$4,500 plus State Base with Master's Degree

Plus a SPED Stipend depending on experience.

Also $334.00 toward Insurance.

How to Apply - Mildred ISD Website under Human Resources and email tidwella@mildredisd.org
